nodes.name: SafeMath

nodes.documentation: @dev Multiplies two numbers, throws on overflow.
nodes.name: mul

nodes.documentation: @dev Integer division of two numbers, truncating the quotient.
nodes.name: div

nodes.documentation: @dev Subtracts two numbers, throws on overflow (i.e. if subtrahend is greater than minuend).
nodes.name: sub

nodes.documentation: @dev Adds two numbers, throws on overflow.
nodes.name: add

nodes.documentation:
@dev Returns the remainder of dividing two unsigned integers. (unsigned integer modulo),
Reverts when dividing by zero.

   * Counterpart to Solidity's `%` operator. This function uses a `revert`
opcode (which leaves remaining gas untouched) while Solidity uses an
invalid opcode to revert (consuming all remaining gas).

   * Requirements:
- The divisor cannot be zero.
nodes.name: mod

nodes.documentation:
@dev Returns the remainder of dividing two unsigned integers. (unsigned integer modulo),
Reverts with custom message when dividing by zero.

   * Counterpart to Solidity's `%` operator. This function uses a `revert`
opcode (which leaves remaining gas untouched) while Solidity uses an
invalid opcode to revert (consuming all remaining gas).

   * Requirements:
- The divisor cannot be zero.
